Rule-Based Chatbot in Python
A simple rule-based chatbot built using Python. This chatbot interacts with users through predefined responses based on user input. It demonstrates the use of conditional statements, loops, functions, and basic date/time handling in Python.
Features
Responds to greetings such as hello and hi
Replies to common questions like:
How are you?
What is your name?
Who made you?
What can you do?
Greets users based on the time of day
Tells a joke
Displays the current date and time
Handles unknown inputs gracefully
Exits the conversation when the user types bye
 Technologies Used
Python 3
Built-in datetime module
